    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="816"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.76/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 26, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>802. Reference Department’s 336, March 15, 1 p.m. Colombian Foreign Office has
                    informed Embassy that Colombian authorities report that frequency 3257.5
                    kilocycles is not assigned to any Colombian station but that the Avianca Radio
                    Station in Medellín which has been assigned a nearby frequency has been ordered
                    to readjust its transmitters in an effort to prevent continuation of the
                    interference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
